t%20the%20sun%20without%20proper%20eye%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Before%20and%20after%20totality%2C%20you%20need%20to%20wear%20eclipse%20glasses%20to%20view%20the%20eclipse%20safely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDirect%20sunlight%20isn't%20good%20for%20your%20camera%20or%20smartphone%20either.%20When%20UV%20radiation%20streams%20directly%20into%20your%20camera%20lens%2C%20it%20can%20cause%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20handholding%20a%20solar%20filter%20for%20iPhone%20cameras.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6614670a1caec1275a6dfa01%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20used%20this%20solar%20filter%20to%20photograph%20the%20partial%20eclipse%20with%20my%20iPhone.%3Cp%3EEllyn%20Lapointe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolar-eclipse-2017-how-to-take-photos-of-the-eclipse-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotect%20your%20equipment%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20photographing%20the%20partial%20eclipse%2C%20you%20need%20to%20use%20an%20ND%20filter%20of%20at%20least%2010%20stops%2C%20and%20preferably%2016%20stops%2C%20Tafreshi%20said.%20ND%20filters%20are%20like%20sunglasses%20for%20your%20camera%3B%20they%20reduce%20the%20intensity%20of%20light%20coming%20into%20your%20lens.%20You%20can%20buy%20a%20solar%20filter%20for%20your%20smartphone%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20purchase%20an%20ND%20filter%20for%20my%20DSLR%20ahead%20of%20time%2C%20so%20I%20only%20used%20that%20camera%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-of-total-solar-eclipse-chile-argentina-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephotographing%20totality%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20when%20it's%20safe%20to%20photograph%20the%20eclipse%20without%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20photos%20of%20the%20partial%20eclipse%2C%20I%20used%20my%20iPhone%20camera%2C%20which%20I%20protected%20with%20a%20spare%20pair%20of%20eclipse%20glasses.%20I%20just%20held%20the%20glasses'%20lens%20over%20my%20iPhone%20camera%20lens%2C%20et%20viola!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Partial%20solar%20eclipse%202024%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6614691116bde8d4ead6c455%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20my%20iPhone%20shots%20of%20the%20partial%20solar%20eclipse.%20In%20addition%20to%20using%20a%20solar%20filter%2C%20I%20used%20an%20app%20called%20Solar%20Snap%20to%20help%20me%20frame%20and%20focus%20my%20shots.%3Cp%3EEllyn%20Lapointe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EKeep%20calm%20and%20use%20a%20tripod%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESolar%20eclipses%20are%20exciting%2C%20especially%20during%20totality%20when%20the%20moon's%20shadow%20completely%20blocks%20out%20the%20sun%20and%20plunges%20you%20into%20darkness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-2024-total-solar-eclipse-cool-best-special-nasa-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etotality%20is%20a%20visceral%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Your%20physical%20reaction%20to%20the%20sudden%20change%20in%20light%20and%20temperature%20can%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20hold%20a%20camera%20steady%20and%20focus%20on%20getting%20the%20right%20shot%2C%20Tafreshi%20said%20in%20an%20email%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20DSLR%20sits%20on%20a%20tripod%20with%20a%20crowd%20of%20people%20in%20the%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661467641caec1275a6dfa40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETo%20make%20sure%20my%20camera%20remained%20stable%2C%20I%20used%20a%20tripod%20while%20shooting%20totality.%3Cp%3EEllyn%20Lapointe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20challenging%20aspect%20%5Bof%20eclipse%20photography%5D%20for%20sure%20is%20how%20to%20control%20your%20senses%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20totality%20affects%20something%20very%20deep%20within%20us%20that%20is%20hard%20to%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20was%20right.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-during-solar-eclipse-diagram-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhen%20totality%20struck%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20drop%20in%20light%20and%20temperature%2C%20the%20beautiful%20sight%20of%20the%20sun's%20corona%2C%20and%20the%20sunset-like%20colors%20on%20the%20horizon.%20It%20took%20me%20a%20moment%20to%20catch%20my%20breath%20and%20refocus%20on%20the%20task%20at%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20sort%20of%20shaking%20or%20vibration%20of%20your%20camera%20will%20ruin%20your%20eclipse%20shot%2C%20Tafreshi%20explained.%20This%20is%20especially%20important%20to%20remember%20during%20totality%20when%20you're%20using%20higher%20exposure.%20If%20you%20anticipate%20shaky%20hands%20during%20the%20experience%2C%20using%20a%20tripod%20is%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20a%2050-inch%20tripod%20to%20keep%20my%20camera%20steady%20while%20I%20took%20totality%20shots.%20It%20did%20help%20keep%20my%20camera%20stable%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20remote%20shutter%20release%20to%20prevent%20movement%20while%20I%20snapped%20photos.%20When%20you%20zoom%20in%2C%20you%20can%20see%20that%20my%20photos%20of%20totality%20are%20slightly%20blurry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221413%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Totality%202024%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661468803f923f7dab05bc4b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22896%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20zoomed-in%20photo%20of%20one%20of%20my%20totality%20shots%2C%20where%20you%20can%20see%20that%20the%20image%20is%20blurry%20due%20to%20camera%20movement%20and%20imperfect%20focus.%3Cp%3EEllyn%20Lapointe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EUse%20manual%20camera%20settings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECellphone%20cameras%20worked%20fine%20during%20the%20eclipse%2C%20but%20those%20who%20used%20a%20regular%20old%20camera%20may%20have%20learned%20it's%20best%20not%20to%20rely%20on%20automatic%20settings%2C%20Tafreshi%20said%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20using%20a%20DSLR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20your%20camera's%20sensor%20may%20get%20confused%20by%20the%20sudden%20drop%20in%20light%20in%20the%20last%20moments%20before%20totality%2C%20Tafreshi%20said.%20Even%20though%20totality%20doesn't%20cause%20total%20darkness%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20drop%20in%20light%20is%20so%20fast%20that%20we%20feel%20it%20is%20becoming%20pitch%20black%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20camera's%20automatic%20settings%20aren't%20able%20to%20adjust%20to%20this%20rapid%20lighting%20change%20quickly.%20Manual%20settings%20offer%20the%20dexterity%20you%20need%20to%20transition%20from%20photographing%20the%20partial%20eclipse%20to%20totality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20to%20capture%20the%20final%20moments%20before%20totality%20(when%20the%20diamond%20ring%20effect%20appears)%2C%20you%20want%20to%20use%20a%20shutter%20speed%20of%20about%201%2F1%2C000%20of%20a%20second.%20But%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20sun's%20last%20rays%20disappear%2C%20you%20need%20to%20switch%20to%20a%20shutter%20speed%20of%200.5%20to%201%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20manual%20settings%20on%20a%20Canon%20Rebel%20T5i%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661465f616bde8d4ead6c2fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20manual%20settings%20I%20used%20to%20shoot%20totality%20with%20my%20Canon%20Rebel%20T5i%20DSLR.%3Cp%3EEllyn%20Lapointe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20shooting%20totality%20with%20my%20DSLR%2C%20I%20set%20my%20ISO%20to%20100%2C%20