%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BCurb%20Your%20Enthusiasm%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20finally%20came%20to%20an%20end%20after%2012%20seasons%20on%20the%20air.%20For%20fans%20of%20Larry%20David's%20long-running%20sitcom%2C%20it%20was%20a%20bittersweet%20but%20fitting%20ending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%2C%20the%20co-creator%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseinfeld-fun-facts-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSeinfeld%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20played%20a%20fictionalized%20version%20of%20himself%20on%20the%20show%20that%20first%20aired%20in%202000.%20The%20series%20finale%20of%20%26quot%3BCurb%26quot%3B%20wrapped%20up%20the%20story%20with%20a%20perfectly%20calibrated%20callback%20to%20the%20ending%20of%20David's%20earlier%20show%2C%20complete%20with%20the%20returns%20of%20some%20memorable%20characters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20did%20the%20'Curb%20Your%20Enthusiasm'%20series%20finale%20end%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20final%20episode%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BNo%20Lessons%20Learned%2C%26quot%3B%20Larry%20faces%20trial%20in%20Atlanta%20after%20violating%20the%20Election%20Integrity%20Act%20of%202021%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20the%20season.%20During%20the%20trial%2C%20the%20district%20attorney%2C%20Earl%20Mack%20(Greg%20Kinnear)%2C%20calls%20character%20witnesses%20to%20testify%20against%20Larry.%20They're%20all%20people%20who%20have%20had%20memorable%20spats%20with%20Larry%20on%20the%20show%20over%20the%20years%2C%20including%20Mocha%20Joe%20(Saverio%20Guerra)%2C%20Irma%20(Tracey%20Ullman)%2C%20and%20Bruce%20Springsteen%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20mirrors%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F12-worst-series-finales-of-all-time-seinfeld-girls-dexter-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20series%20finale%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20that%20episode%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20Finale%2C%26quot%3B%20past%20characters%20from%20throughout%20the%20show's%20nine%20seasons%20returned%20as%20character%20witnesses%20after%20Jerry%20(Jerry%20Seinfeld)%2C%20George%20(Jason%20Alexander)%2C%20Elaine%20(Julia%20Louis-Dreyfus)%2C%20and%20Kramer%20(Michael%20Richards)%20were%20arrested%20and%20put%20on%20trial%20for%20violating%20a%20local%20Good%20Samaritan%20law%20in%20a%20small%20Massachusetts%20town%20when%20they%20didn't%20intervene%20to%20help%20a%20man%20getting%20car-jacked.%20Much%20like%20Larry%20being%20confronted%20by%20the%20many%20people%20who%20hate%20him%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20also%20crew%20faced%20ghosts%20from%20their%20past%20dredging%20up%20their%20bad%20behavior%20during%20their%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20twist%20is%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flarry-david-almost-didnt-make-another-curb-your-enthusiasm-season-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BCurb%20Your%20Enthusiasm%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20ending%20differs.%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20ends%20with%20the%20four%20leads%20being%20found%20guilty%20and%20sentenced%20to%20a%20year%20in%20prison%3B%20the%20last%20we%20see%20of%20them%2C%20they're%20all%20actually%20serving%20out%20their%20sentences.%20A%20conversation%20they%20have%20in%20the%20jail%20cell%20is%20a%20callback%20to%20a%20conversation%20in%20the%20very%20first%20episode%20of%20the%20series.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarry%20is%20also%20found%20guilty%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BCurb%26quot%3B%20finale%20and%20similarly%20sentenced%20to%20a%20year%20in%20prison.%20He%20has%20a%20conversation%20complaining%20about%20his%20%26quot%3Bpants%20tent%26quot%3B%20that's%20a%20call-back%20to%20a%20conversation%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20the%20show%20and%20that%20episode's%20title.%20But%20that's%20where%20the%20two%20comedies%20diverge.%20Instead%20of%20leaving%20Larry%20in%20prison%2C%20Jerry%20Seinfeld%20(playing%20a%20version%20of%20himself)%20shows%20up%2C%20having%20previously%20run%20into%20Larry%20earlier%20in%20the%20episode%2C%20and%20informs%20Larry%20that%20one%20of%20the%20jurors%20in%20his%20trial%20broke%20his%20sequester.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20resulting%20mistrial%20gets%20Larry%20out%20of%20prison.%20Then%2C%20things%20get%20meta.%20As%20he's%20picking%20him%20up%2C%20Seinfeld%20tells%20Larry%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20end%20up%20like%20this.%20Nobody%20wants%20to%20see%20it.%20Trust%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarry%20tells%20Seinfeld%20that%20%26quot%3Bthis%20is%20how%20we%20should've%20ended%20the%20finale%2C%26quot%3B%20referencing%20the%20widely%20hated%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20finale.%20Both%20kick%20themselves%20for%20not%20thinking%20of%20this%20ending%20back%20when%20that%20show%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCurb%26quot%3B%20ends%20with%20Larry%20on%20a%20flight%20back%20home%20with%20his%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221708%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Larry%20David%20and%20Jerry%20Seinfeld%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BCurb%20Your%20Enthusiasm%26quot%3B%20series%20finale%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661465ba1caec1275a6df99e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221281%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJerry%20Seinfeld%20and%20Larry%20David%20in%20the%20series%20finale%20of%20%26quot%3BCurb%20Your%20Enthusiasm.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EJohn%20Johnson%2FHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20really%20hated%20the%20'Seinfeld'%20ending%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20over%2025%20years%20since%20the%20series%20finale%20of%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20aired%20on%20May%2014%2C%201998.%20Despite%20the%20fact%20that%20decades%20have%20passed%2C%20some%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F1998%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fnothing-works-for-nbc-1117470932%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E76.3%20million%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20tuned%20in%20are%20still%20mad%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20critics%20hated%20it%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Few.com%2Farticle%2F1998%2F05%2F29%2Fseinfeld-5%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEntertainment%20Weekly's%20Ken%20Tucker%3C%2Fa%3E%20gave%20the%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20series%20finale%20a%20C-%2C%20calling%20David%20(who'd%20left%20the%20show%20after%20the%20seventh%20season%20but%20returned%20to%20write%20the%20finale)%20a%20%26quot%3Bspiteful%2C%20unforgiving%20moralist%26quot%3B%20for%20making%20the%20main%20characters%20%26quot%3Bpay%20for%20all%20their%20years%20of%20selfishness%2C%20self-absorption%2C%20immaturity%2C%20and%20greed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20the%20episode's%20start%20(an%20oddly%20paced%20coffee-shop%20scene)%20to%20an%20ending%20that%20was%20like%20a%20Samuel%20Beckett%20first%20draft%2C%20the%20show's%20swan%20song%20was%20off-key%20and%20bloated%2C%26quot%3B%20Tucker%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20Seinfeld%20himself%20had%20some%20regrets%20about%20the%20divisive%20ending.%20%26quot%3BI%20sometimes%20think%20we%20really%20shouldn't%20have%20even%20done%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20at%20the%20New%20Yorker%20Festival%20in%202017%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vulture.com%2F2017%2F10%2Fjerry-seinfeld-sometimes-regrets-seinfeld-finale.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVulture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20on%20us%20at%20that%20time%20to%20do%20one%20big%20last%20show%2C%20but%20big%20is%20always%20bad%20in%20comedy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20even%20though%20some%20are%20now%20saying%20David%20%26quot%3Bfixed%26quot%3B%20things%20with%20the%20twist%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BCurb%26quot%3B%20ending%2C%20the%20comedian%20has%20been%20a%20defender%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20series%20finale%20all%20along.%20In%20season%20seven%20of%20%26quot%3BCurb%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20the%20main%20cast%20of%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20appeared%20for%20an%20arc%20where%20they%20reunited%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20up%20for%20the%20finale%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20fictionalized%20Larry%20insisted%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20good%20finale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20has%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20bad%20reception%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BSeinfeld%26quot%3B%20finale%20even%20took%20the%20pressure%20off%20for%20him%20wrapping%20up%20%26quot%3BCurb%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20way%20%E2%80%94%20which%20makes%20it%20even%20more%20clever%20how%20he%20brought%20that%20ending%20back%20for%20a%20re-do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20so%20much%20grief%20from%20the%20'Seinfeld'%20finale%2C%20which%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20intensely%20disliked%2C%20that%20I%20no%20longer%20feel%20a%20need%20to%20wrap%20things%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrantland.com%2Fhollywood-prospectus%2Fb-s-report-larry-david-on-the-future-of-curb-your-enthusiasm-and-the-seinfeld-finale%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGrantland%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202014%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20thought%20the%20conceit%20for%20bringing%20back%20all%20the%20characters%20in%20the%20finale%20trial%20was%20%26quot%3Bclever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20that%20gimmick%20worked%20better%20this%20time%20around%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BNo%20Lessons%20Learned%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0264235%2Fepisodes%2F%3FtopRated%3DDESC%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighest-rated%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BCurb%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20IMDb%20as%20of%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcurb-your-enthusiasm-series-finale-ending-recap-seinfeld-reference-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712614761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6614301516bde8d4ead6a5f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2