b05b8d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221081%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Devil%20comet%20(left)%20shines%20bright%20green%20as%20it%20streaks%20through%20the%20sky.%20Though%20it%20could%20have%20been%20during%20totality%20(right)%20I%20wasn't%20able%20to%20see%20or%20photograph%20it.%3Cp%3EDan%20Bartlett%2C%20Damien%20Deltenre%2C%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEclipse%20watchers%20were%20hoping%20to%20catch%20a%20glimpse%20of%20comet%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%20during%20the%20total%20solar%20eclipse.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20wanted%20to%20get%20a%20picture%20of%20it%2C%20so%20I%20reached%20out%20to%20astrophotographer%20Dan%20Bartlett%20for%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20even%20with%20his%20best%20advice%2C%20I%20wasn't%20able%20to%20get%20the%20shot.%20Here's%20where%20it%20all%20went%20wrong.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weeks%20leading%20up%20to%20Monday's%20total%20solar%20eclipse%20became%20even%20more%20exciting%20when%20astronomers%20announced%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevil-comet-visible-during-total-solar-eclipse-how-see-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomet%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BDevil%20comet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20might%20be%20visible%20during%20totality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20massive%20comet%20is%20the%20size%20of%20Mount%20Everest%2C%20burns%20bright%20green%2C%20and%20gets%20its%20name%20for%20the%20horn-like%20shape%20of%20its%20coma.%20So%2C%20of%20course%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20see%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20that%20%E2%80%94%20I%20wanted%20to%20try%20to%20get%20a%20picture%20of%20it.%20But%20I%20knew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreen-comet-ztf-what-look-like-see-photos-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephotographing%20a%20comet%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20no%20easy%20feat.%20They're%20unpredictable%2C%20moving%20objects%20that%20can%20either%20be%20stunningly%20visible%20or%20near%20impossible%20to%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20turned%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolar-eclipse-photos-totality-us-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessional%20astrophotographer%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAdvice%20from%20a%20comet%20photographer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Bartlett%20has%20taken%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.astrobin.com%2Fusers%2Fh2ologg%2F%3Fsub%3Duploaded%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20photos%20of%20comets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-this-astrophotographer-takes-stunning-photos-of-our-solar-system-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETo%20create%20his%20striking%20images%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20uses%20high-tech%20equipment%2C%20including%20huge%20telescopes%20with%20sky-tracking%20scopes%2C%20and%20advanced%20photo-processing%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Copet%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%20streaking%20across%20a%20dark%2C%20starry%20sky%20with%20a%20bright%20yellow%20star%20shining%20on%20the%20upper%20left.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660d522c3f923f7dab03fdf2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221709%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20is%20one%20of%20Bartlett's%20most%20recent%20photos%20of%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%2C%20taken%20using%20a%20telescope%20and%20a%20sky%20tracking%20scope.%20%3Cp%3EDan%20Bartlett%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20his%20professional%20skills%20and%20equipment%2C%20photographing%20comets%20can%20be%20difficult.%20Bartlett%20said%20he%20encounters%20%26quot%3Bevery%20challenge%20you%20could%20imagine%2C%26quot%3B%20from%20his%20scope%20not%20working%20to%20not%20being%20able%20to%20get%20the%20comet%20in%20focus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20me%2C%20I'm%20an%20amateur%20with%20only%20a%20standard%20DSLR%2C%20a%20tripod%2C%20and%20my%20iPhone.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolar-eclipse-cloudy-weather-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eif%20the%20weather%20was%20clear%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20comet%20was%20visible%2C%20I'd%20still%20have%20a%20chance%20of%20getting%20the%20shot%2C%20Bartlett%20said%2C%20as%20long%20as%20I%20paid%20attention%20to%20three%20things%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKnowing%20where%20to%20look.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20comet%20is%20hard%20to%20photograph%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20where%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EISO%20rating.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Bartlett%20suggested%20I%20set%20my%20ISO%20around%201%2C000%20-%201%2C600.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChoose%20the%20right%20exposure.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20photographing%20comets%2C%20your%20exposure%20should%20be%20short%20enough%20that%20the%20comet%20isn't%20blurry%2C%20but%20the%20right%20setting%20depends%20on%20the%20speed%20of%20the%20comet%20and%20the%20focal%20length%20of%20the%20camera.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhere%20it%20all%20went%20wrong%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20the%20darkness%20of%20totality%2C%20I%20wasn't%20able%20to%20spot%20the%20%26quot%3BDevil%20comet%26quot%3B%20with%20my%20naked%20eye%20or%20my%20camera.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I'd%20had%20a%20telescope%20or%20binoculars%2C%20I%20might%20have%20been%20able%20to%20use%20them%20to%20locate%20the%20comet%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20and%20then%20direct%20my%20camera's%20zoom%20lens%20toward%20it.%20But%20instead%2C%20I%20shot%20vaguely%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20where%20I%20thought%20the%20comet%20might%20be%2C%20and%20only%20captured%20darkness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20I%20was%20amazed%20by%20how%20quickly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolar-eclipse-map-nasa-where-when-see-path-of-totality-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etotality%3C%2Fa%3E%20whizzed%20by.%20During%20this%20window%2C%20I%20was%20also%20trying%20to%20snap%20photos%20of%20t