202024%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cntraveler.com%2Fstory%2Fairline-checked-baggage-fees-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECond%C3%A9%20Nast%20Traveler.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20common%20%E2%80%94%20and%20avoidable%20%E2%80%94%20mistakes%20CiCi%20sees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECiCi%20said%20the%20biggest%20mistake%20she's%20seen%20is%20when%20travelers%20pack%20their%20bags%20so%20full%20that%20they%20can't%20lift%20them%20into%20overhead%20bins.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20lifts%20their%20luggage%20into%20an%20overhead%20bin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62728dbbc3fd45001951f44f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20person%20lifting%20their%20luggage%20into%20an%20overhead%20bin.%3Cp%3EPONG%20HANDSOME%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20she%20constantly%20sees%20passengers%20who%20can't%20pick%20up%20their%20carry-on%20bags%20and%20must%20ask%20for%20help%20from%20other%20passengers%20or%20a%20flight%20attendant.%20But%20she%20stressed%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-you-should-never-do-on-planes-flight-attendant-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elifting%20suitcases%20is%20not%20part%20of%20her%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20she%20doesn't%20want%20to%20risk%20hurting%20herself%20by%20lifting%20someone%20else's%20bag.%20Airlines%20can%20have%20policies%20preventing%20flight%20attendants%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftravel%2F2023%2F05%2F15%2Fflight-attendant-lifting-bags%2F%5C%22%3Elifting%20passengers'%20suitcases%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20that%20if%20a%20flight%20attendant%20gets%20injured%20while%20helping%20with%20suitcases%2C%20they%20may%20not%20receive%20worker's%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20passengers%20should%20be%20confident%20and%20comfortable%20lifting%20their%20luggage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20airlines%2C%20like%20Frontier%20Airlines%20and%20Hawaiian%20Airlines%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftravel.usnews.com%2Ffeatures%2Fcarry-on-luggage-sizes-size-restrictions-by-airline%5C%22%3Erules%20about%20how%20much%20your%20suitcase%20can%20weigh%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20if%20your%20bag%20is%20overstuffed%20and%20weighs%20too%20much%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20airline%2C%20you%20might%20have%20to%20check%20it%20at%20the%20gate.%20This%20can%20add%20unwanted%20time%20to%20your%20travel%2C%20CiCi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EShe%20said%20passengers%20need%20to%20stop%20bringing%20more%20than%20two%20bags%20on%20the%20plane.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20pulls%20two%20bags%20through%20an%20airport.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6272991ec3fd45001951f7a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20person%20pulling%20two%20bags%20through%20an%20airport.%3Cp%3Etrattieritratti%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20she%20often%20sees%20people%20flying%20with%20a%20roller%20suitcase%2C%20a%20backpack%2C%20and%20a%20purse%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20one%20too%20many%20carry-on%20bags%2C%20according%20to%20airline%20rules%2C%20which%20can%20result%20in%20gate%20agents%20asking%20passengers%20to%20consolidate%20their%20belongings%20into%20two%20bags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20airlines%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftraveltips.usatoday.com%2Fluggage-limits-international-air-travel-109889.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallow%20passengers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20store%20one%20item%20in%20the%20overhead%20bin%20and%20fit%20one%20personal%20item%20below%20the%20seat%20in%20front%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20passengers%20should%20fit%20their%20belongings%20into%20the%20allotted%20number%20of%20bags%20for%20their%20airline%2C%20noting%20that%20some%20airlines%20charge%20extra%20for%20carry-on%20suitcases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPassengers%20whose%20essentials%20aren't%20easily%20accessible%20can%20cause%20boarding%20delays.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22CiCi%20said%20keep%20things%20like%20your%20book%20in%20your%20personal%20item%20%E2%80%94%20not%20your%20carry-on%20suitcase.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62729a9bf6bd4b0019cb5c9f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECiCi%20said%20to%20keep%20things%20like%20your%20book%20in%20your%20personal%20item%2C%20not%20your%20carry-on%20suitcase.%3Cp%3ESolStock%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20passengers%20who%20need%20to%20access%20their%20carry-on%20suitcases%20can%20sometimes%20cause%20delays%20in%20boarding.%20She%20tells%20passengers%20to%20pack%20everything%20they%20need%20for%20a%20flight%20in%20their%20personal%20item.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20put%20things%20that%20they%20need%20on%20the%20plane%20%E2%80%94%20like%20their%20book%20and%20their%20earbuds%20or%20whatever%20they're%20going%20to%20need%20%E2%80%94%20inside%20their%20suitcase%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it's%20not%20easy%20to%20access.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20passenger%20who%20has%20to%20get%20in%20their%20suitcase%20and%20sift%20through%20their%20belongings%20during%20boarding%20can%20block%20other%20passengers%20from%20their%20seats%20and%20cause%20delays%2C%20CiCi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaiting%20until%20they're%20in%20midair%20to%20get%20items%20from%20their%20suitcase%20is%20risky%20too%20%E2%80%94%20turbulence%20could've%20shifted%20the%20bags%20in%20the%20overhead%20bin%2C%20which%20might%20cause%20them%20to%20fall%20and%20injure%20someone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20her%20advice%20is%20to%20make%20sure%20all%20your%20flight%20essentials%20are%20in%20your%20personal%20item%2C%20which%20will%20be%20within%20reach%20during%20the%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMany%20passengers%20don't%20pack%20their%20liquids%20correctly.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20transfers%20toiletries%20into%20smaller%20containers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6272a4a0f6bd4b0019cb603b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20person%20transferring%20toiletries%20into%20smaller%20containers.%3Cp%3EShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changing%20altitudes%20an%20airplane%20experiences%20cause%20gases%20to%20expand%20during%20a%20flight%2C%20which%20can%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20cause%20toiletries%20or%20water%20bottles%20to%20leak%20in%20your%20carry-on%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthepointsguy.com%2Fguide%2Fkeep-toiletries-from-leaking%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20Points%20Guy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20that%20in%20her%20experience%20observing%20passengers'%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tsa.gov%2Ftravel%2Fsecurity-screening%2Fliquids-rule%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETSA-approved%20liquids%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Bpeople's%20stuff%20leaks%20all%20over%20the%20place.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20she%20had%20a%20few%20tips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20squeeze%20as%20much%20air%20out%20of%20the%20bottle%20as%20possible.%20She%20said%20this%20would%20help%20prevent%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20most%20importantly%2C%20she%20said%2C%20choose%20travel-sized%20containers%20wisely.%20CiCi%20said%20that%20she's%20tried%20dozens%20of%20travel-sized%20containers%20designed%20to%20prevent%20leaks%20and%20that%20the%20ones%20she's%20had%20the%20most%20success%20with%20have%20screw-on%20caps%20instead%20of%20snap%20tops.%20She%20said%20she%20thinks%20these%20create%20a%20tighter%20seal%20to%20help%20prevent%20leaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPassengers%20make%20the%20mistake%20of%20not%20packing%20a%20reusable%20water%20bottle.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20fills%20up%20their%20reusable%20water%20bottle%20at%20an%20airport.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F627290fff6bd4b0019cb5975%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22937%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20person%20filling%20up%20their%20reusable%20water%20bottle%20at%20an%20airport.%3Cp%3Emyboys.me%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20stay%20hydrated%20on%20a%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%228d6915a88c8ecb8cb02ccefe1da4ab77%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.asma.org%2Fasma%2Fmedia%2Fasma%2FTravel-Publications%2FHEALTH-TIPS-FOR-AIRLINE-TRAVEL-Trifold-2013.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Aerospace%20Medical%20Association%20recommends%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20travelers%20drink%208%20ounces%20of%20water%20each%20hour%20on%20a%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20you%20can't%20bring%20more%20than%203%20ounces%20of%20liquids%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20you%20can%20bring%20a%20frozen%20water%20bottle%20or%20an%20empty%20water%20bottle%20you%20can%20fill%20once%20you're%20inside%20the%20airport%20terminal%2C%20CiCi%20said.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tsa.gov%2Ftravel%2Fsecurity-screening%2Fwhatcanibring%2Fitems%2Fice%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Transportation%20Security%20Administration%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20solid%20frozen%20liquids%20are%20allowed%20through%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EShe%20said%20some%20travelers%20forget%20to%20pack%20their%20own%20snacks.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20eats%20an%20apple%20on%20an%20airplane.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62729098c3fd45001951f4fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20woman%20eating%20an%20apple%20on%20an%20airplane.%3Cp%3Efrantic00%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20turbulence%20during%20the%20summer%20can%20get%20intense%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.planeandpilotmag.com%2Farticle%2Fthe-season-of-turbulence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Plane%20%26amp%3B%20Pilot%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20high%20heat%20causes%20more%20convective%20turbulence%20in%20the%20sky.%20CiCi%20said%20that%20when%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20turbulence%2C%20flight%20attendants%20are%20sometimes%20required%20to%20be%20seated%20for%20an%20entire%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20flight%20attendants%20can't%20get%20up%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-you-should-avoid-buying-on-planes-flight-attendant-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassengers%20don't%20get%20snacks%20or%20beverages%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20airlines%2C%20like%20Frontier%20Airlines%20and%20Allegiant%20Air%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthepointsguy.com%2Fnews%2Finflight-service-resuming%2F%5C%22%3Editched%20the%20complimentary%20snack%20service%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20offer%20drinks%20and%20snacks%20for%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20suggests%20passengers%20be%20prepared%20with%20their%20own%20snacks.%20She%20said%20that%20beyond%20fruits%20like%20apples%20and%20oranges%2C%20she%20always%20has%20a%20few%20bags%20of%20nuts%20in%20her%20luggage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECiCi%20said%20she%20sometimes%20sees%20passengers%20packing%20heavy%20items%20instead%20of%20wearing%20them%20on%20the%20plane.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221085%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20wears%20a%20jacket%20in%20an%20airport.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62729027f6bd4b0019cb593d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22814%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20woman%20wearing%20a%20jacket%20in%20an%20airport.%3Cp%3EDmitry%20Marchenko%2FEyeEm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECiCi%20said%20that%20if%20you're%20flying%20with%20just%20a%20carry-on%2C%20wear%20your%20heavy%20items%20on%20the%20plane%20instead%20of%20packing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she's%20sometimes%20shocked%20to%20speak%20to%20passengers%20who%20are%20traveling%20far%20with%20just%20a%20carry-on%20and%20wearing%20light%20airplane%20attire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20what%20CiCi%20does.%20She%20said%20that%20on%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fitalians-share-tourist-free-destinations-to-visit-in-italy-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflight%20to%20Italy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20wore%20her%20bulky%20rain%20boots%2C%20a%20sweater%2C%20and%20a%20jacket%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20she%20was%20flying%20out%20of%20hot%2C%20humid%20Florida.%20She%20added%20that%20this%20saved%20her%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20space%20in%20her%20carry-on%20and%20allowed%20her%20to%20pack%20more%20outfits%20for%20her%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-carry-on-suitcase-packing-mistakes-2022-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712611086000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66144f0e3f923f7dab05ae00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-carry-on-suitcase-packing-mistakes-2022-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CiCi%2C%20a