0the%20universe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year's%20path%20of%20totality%20is%20115%20miles%20(185%20kilometers)%20wide%20and%20home%20to%20nearly%2032%20million%20Americans%2C%20with%20an%20additional%20150%20million%20living%20less%20than%20200%20miles%20from%20the%20strip.%20Those%20further%20away%20can%20still%20enjoy%20a%20partial%20eclipse%2C%20or%20follow%20a%20webcast%20provided%20by%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsolar-eclipse-2024-explained-what-makes-todays-total-solar-eclipse-surya-grahan-2024-so-rare-5396890%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etotal%20solar%20eclipse%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20can%20be%20seen%20from%20a%20large%20part%20of%20North%20America%20won't%20come%20around%20until%202044.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EFestivals%2C%20flights%2C%20romance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20are%20capitalizing%20on%20the%20excitement%20with%20special%20events%2C%20while%20hotels%20and%20short-term%20rentals%20in%20prime%20viewing%20locations%20have%20been%20booked%20solid%20for%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Stonehenge%20II%20park%20in%20Ingram%2C%20Texas%2C%20a%20replica%20of%20the%20prehistoric%20structure%20in%20England%2C%20eclipse%20watchers%20had%20gathered%20from%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20our%20third%20solar%20eclipse%2C%26quot%3B%2062-year-old%20Jim%20Saltigerald%2C%20who%20was%20attending%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20two%20children%2C%20told%20AFP.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20all%20praying%20and%20hoping%20that%20we%20have%20a%20good%20break%20in%20the%20clouds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Cleveland%2C%20where%20local%20officials%20expect%20some%20200%2C000%20visitors%2C%20the%20Rock%20%26amp%3B%20Roll%20Hall%20of%20Fame%20plans%20a%20four-day%20%26quot%3BSolarfest%26quot%3B%20of%20live%20music.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20Russellville%2C%20Arkansas%2C%20more%20than%20300%20couples%20are%20re