0%26quot%3Blike%20capital%20punishment%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabib%20Ahmed%20Khan%20moved%20the%20top%20court%20seeking%20permanent%20parole%20given%20his%20deteriorating%20health%20and%20age%2C%20and%20a%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Abhay%20S%20Oka%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20asked%20the%20Rajasthan%20government%20to%20consider%20his%20case%20from%20the%20human%20rights%20angle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20counsel%20said%20he%20has%20been%20in%20jail%20for%20over%2027%20years%20after%20which%20he%20was%20granted%20parole%20thrice.%20The%20third%20parole%20is%20being%20now%20extended%20by%20this%20court%20from%20time%20to%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20which%20perused%20Mr%20Khan's%20medical%20reports%2C%20asked%20what%20purpose%20will%20be%20served%20by%20his%20incarceration%20at%20this%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20see%20his%20medical%20report.%20Where%20will%20he%20go%3F%20It's%20the%20worst.%20Yes%2C%20he%20was%20convicted%20for%20a%20terror%20offence%20but%20he%20was%20not%20awarded%20capital%20punishment.%20Continued%20incarceration%20for%20him%20is%20like%20capital%20punishment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20told%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20(ASG)%20Vikramjeet%20Banerjee%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Rajasthan%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20asked%20Mr%20Banerjee%20to%20consider%20his%20remission%20and%20see%20the%20case%20from%20a%20human%20rights%20angle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ASG%20submitted%20that%20for%20remission%2C%20the%20convict%20has%20to%20make%20an%20application%20to%20the%20state%20government%20but%20in%20this%20case%2C%20his%20conviction%20for%20terror%20offence%20would%20be%20a%20hindrance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20what%20is%20Article%2021%20in%20the%20Constitution%20for%2C%20Justice%20Oka%20asked%2C%20adding%20that%20Mr%20Khan%20can%20neither%20walk%20nor%20see%20properly%20according%20to%20his%20medical%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Bhuyan%20said%20that%20at%2096%2C%20Mr%20Khan%20is%20just%20counting%20his%20days%20and%20the%20law%20cannot%20be%20so%20insensitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20court%20has%20all%20the%20powers%20in%20the%20world%20and%20if%20it%20were%20to%20use%20the%20power%20under%20Article%20142%20of%20the%20Constitution%20for%20remission%2C%20then%20I%20would%20urge%20not%20to%20do%20so.%20Because%20remission%20can%20only%20be%20granted%20by%20the%20state%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ASG%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20all%20the%20powers%20in%20the%20world%20but%20all%20the%20powers%20under%20the%20Constitution.%20Ultimately%2C%20there%20has%20to%20be%20some%20balance%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Oka%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20asked%20Mr%20Banerjee%20to%20seek%20instruction%20on%20whether%20Habib%20Ahmed%20Khan%20could%20be%20granted%20remission%20or%20permanent%20parole%20and%20listed%20the%20matter%20for%20hearing%20after%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabib%20Ahmed%20Khan%20was%20arrested%20in%201994%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20series%20of%20train%20blasts%20in%201993%20and%20was%20convicted%20in%202004%20by%20the%20Ajmer%20trial%20court%20along%20with%2014%20others%20under%20the%20Terrorist%20and%20Disruptive%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(TADA).%20His%20conviction%20and%20life%20sentence%20were%20upheld%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202016%20and%20he%20was%20lodged%20in%20Jaipur%20jail%20before%20being%20granted%20parole%20in%202021%20by%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202018%2C%20the%20Rajasthan%20High%20Court%20granted%20him%20parole%20for%20the%20first%20time%20for%2020%20days%20while%20taking%20into%20consideration%20his%20age%20and%20that%20a%20co-accused%20in%20the%20same%20case%2C%20Asfaq%20Khan%2C%20was%20granted%20parole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Khan%20was%20again%20granted%20parole%20for%2020%20days%20in%202020%20with%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20coronavirus%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20granted%20the%20third%20parole%20in%20February%202021%20by%20the%20High%20Court%20for%20three%20weeks%2C%20which%20was%20being%20extended%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20so%20far%20due%20to%20his%20deteriorating%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712591700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fcq5c2cmg_supreme-court-reuters_625x300_06_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F1993-train-blasts-convict-habib-ahmed-khan-release-like-capital-punishment-supreme-court-on-man-96-serving-life-sentence-5400916%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20favoured%20remission%20to%20an%20ailing%2096-year-old%20convict%20serving%20life%20term%20in%20the%201993%20Rajasthan%20train%20blast%20case%20and%20currently%20on%20parole%2C%20saying%20continued%20incarceration%20is%20%26quot%3Blike%20capital%20punishment%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F1993-train-blasts-convict-habib-ahmed-khan-release-like-capital-punishment-supreme-court-on-man-96-serving-life-sentence-5400916%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F1993-train-blasts-convict-habib-ahmed-khan-release-like-capital-punishment-supreme-court-on-man-96-serving-life-sentence-5400916%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F1993-train-blasts-convict-habib-ahmed-khan-release-like-capital-punishment-supreme-court-on-man-96-serving-life-sentence-5400916%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Preity%20shares%20picts%20from%20her%20first%20photoshoot%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712591635000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109141037%2Cimgsize-25604.