20to%20reflect%20on%20our%20place%20in%20the%20universe%2C%20scientists%20have%20been%20studying%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20sun%20and%20the%20formation%20of%20our%20solar%20system%20for%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20solar%20system%20today%20is%20mainly%20composed%20of%20a%20central%20star%20-%20the%20sun%20-%20along%20with%20an%20inner%20solar%20system%20with%20rocky%20planets%2C%20and%20an%20outer%20solar%20system%20with%20gas%20and%20ice%20giant%20planets.%20However%2C%20it%20hasn't%20always%20been%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20was%20the%20sun%20formed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20solar%20system%20formed%20from%20the%20gravitational%20collapse%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bdense%26quot%3B%20giant%20molecular%20cloud%20of%20gas%20and%20dust%2C%20composed%20mainly%20of%20hydrogen%2C%20a%20bit%20of%20helium%2C%20and%20about%20one%20per%20cent%20of%20heavier%20elements.%20After%20the%20cloud%20collapsed%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20mass%20concentrated%20onto%20the%20centre%2C%20creating%20our%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20star%20continued%20to%20contract%20until%20it%20reached%20its%20final%20size%20and%20density.%20Hydrogen%20fusion%20ignited%20the%20sun's%20core%2C%20causing%20the%20star%20to%20emit%20light%20and%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20sun%2C%20the%20leftovers%20-%20about%200.5%20to%20one%20per%20cent%20of%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1088%2F0004-637X%2F771%2F2%2F129%5C%22%3E%20mass%20of%20the%20sun%3C%2Fa%3E%20-%20created%20a%20protoplanetary%20disk%2C%20where%20planets%20subsequently%20formed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProtoplanetary%20disks%20in%20the%20process%20of%20making%20planets%20are%20not%20just%20theory%20-%20they%20have%20actually%20been%20observed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sci.news%2Fastronomy%2Fscience-alma-planet-formation-young-star-hl-tauri-02259.html%5C%22%3Esuch%20as%20the%20disk%20around%20HL%20Tauri%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20young%20star%20with%20rings%20and%20gaps%20that%20are%20likely%20signs%20of%20forming%20planets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20pretty%20good%20idea%20of%20when%20that%20collapse%20took%20place%20in%20our%20solar%20system%20because%20we%20can%20analyze%20the%20first%20(or%20oldest)%20solids%20that%20condensed%20out%20from%20the%20protoplanetary%20disk%20gas.%20This%20detailed%20analysis%20is%20only%20possible%20in%20our%20solar%20system%2C%20since%20we%20cannot%20directly%20collect%20material%20from%20other%20solar%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20solid%20fragments%2C%20called%20calcium-aluminum%20rich%20inclusions%20(CAIs)%2C%20have%20been%20found%20in%20some%20of%20the%20oldest%20meteorites%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.gca.2016.10.044%5C%22%3Eage%20dated%20to%204%2C567.3%20million%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20when%20our%20solar%20system%20came%20into%20being%2C%20and%20provides%20the%20age%20for%20the%20birth%20of%20our%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EElement%20factories%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVery%20dense%20molecular%20clouds%20can%20collapse%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpweb.cfa.harvard.edu%2Fresearch%2Ftopic%2Finterstellar-medium-and-molecular-clouds%5C%22%3Edue%20to%20their%20own%20gravity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20the%20collapse%20of%20our%20protosolar%20nebula%20was%20likely%20triggered%20by%20the%20perturbation%20from%20the%20passing%20shock%20wave%20of%20an%20exploding%20massive%20star%2C%20called%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fscience%2Fsupernova%5C%22%3Esupernova%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20shock%20wave%20compressed%20enough%20of%20the%20molecular%20cloud%20to%20start%20collapsing%20it%2C%20and%20form%20a%20central%20star%20and%20a%20planetary%20disk%20around%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20for%20this%20hypothesis%20is%20found%20in%20the%20isotope%20composition%20of%20some%20chemical%20elements%20in%20pre-solar%20grains.%20Pre-solar%20grains%20are%20tiny%20silicon-carbide%20minerals%20(under%20a%20micrometre%20in%20size)%2C%20and%20can%20be%20found%20in%20parts%20per%20million%20quantities%20in%20some%20meteorites.%20These%20pre-solar%20grains%20have%20isotope%20compositions%20that%20cannot%20be%20explained%20by%20chemical%20or%20physical%20processes%20occurring%20in%20our%20solar%20system%2C%20and%20are%20better%20explained%20by%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.2343%2Fgeochemj.2.0401%5C%22%3Egrains%20forming%20elsewhere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20isotope%20composition%20of%20pre-solar%20grains%20implies%20that%2C%20after%20the%20supernova%2C%20these%20grains%20travelled%20into%20space%2C%20and%20they%20got%20trapped%20into%20our%20molecular%20cloud%2C%20which%20then%20collapsed%2C%20keeping%20those%20grains%20inside%20the%20meteorites%20that%20we%20study%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20much%20older%20is%20the%20sun%20than%20the%20Earth%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20age%20of%204%2C567%20million%20years%20found%20for%20the%20CAIs%20is%20often%20used%20as%20the%20age%20of%20the%20Earth.%20However%2C%20after%20the%20formation%20of%20CAIs%2C%20it%20likely%20took%20tens%20to%20a%20few%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20years%20for%20Earth%20to%20form.%20Although%20we%20have%20determined%20the%20age%20of%20our%20solar%20system%20very%20precisely%2C%20debates%20still%20persist%20regarding%20the%20age%20of%20our%20own%20planet%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20comes%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Earth%20is%20an%20active%20planet%2C%20and%20is%20very%20efficient%20at%20recycling%20and%20reworking%20its%20oldest%20rocks%2C%20resetting%20their%20geochronological%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2098%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20proto-Earth's%20mass%20might%20have%20been%20already%20melded%20together%20by%20the%20time%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs43017-022-00370-0%5C%22%3Egiant%20impact%20hit%20the%20proto-Earth%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20giant%20impact%20added%20the%20remaining%20two%20per%20cent%20to%20Earth%2C%20and%20also%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2F35089010%5C%22%3Eformation%20of%20our%20moon.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20giant%20impact%2C%20occurring%20somewhere%20between%2070%20to%20120%20million%20years%20after%20the%20CAIs%20formation%2C%20could%20provide%20the%20best%20determination%20for%20the%20age%20of%20the%20Earth.%20Independent%20age%20estimates%20can%20also%20be%20obtained%20from%20estimating%20the%20timing%20of%20Earth's%20magma%20ocean%20solidification%2C%20a%20consequence%20of%20the%20moon-forming%20giant%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudies%20attempting%20to%20determine%20the%20timing%20of%20magma%20ocean%20solidification%20provide%20ages%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1002%2F9781118860359.ch8%5C%22%3Ebetween%20100%20and%20150%20million%20years%20after%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20upcoming%20total%20solar%20eclipse%20is%20an%20opportunity%20for%20everyone%20to%20appreciate%20the%20wonders%20of%20our%20solar%20system%2C%20which%20took%20about%204.6%20billion%20years%20to%20evolve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20truly%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fsolar-eclipses-result-from-a-fantastic-celestial-coincidence-of-scale-and-distance-224113%5C%22%3Ecosmic%20coincidence%20that%20total%20solar%20eclipses%20can%20be%20seen%20on%20Earth%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20the%20sun%20happens%20to%20be%20about%20400%20times%20larger%20than%20the%20moon%2C%20which%20is%20400%20times%20closer%20than%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20were%20on%20Mars%20or%20Venus%2C%20you%20would%20not%20be%20so%20lucky%20as%20to%20witness%20this%20phenomenon!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegiescience.edu%2Fdr-johanna-teske-0%5C%22%3EJohanna%20Teske%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Carnegie%20Institution%20for%20Science%20contributed%20to%20writing%20this%20article.%20She%20is%20a%20staff%20scientist%2C%20and%20researches%20the%20compositions%20of%20exoplanets.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712577840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F3311735o_sun_625x300_08_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-how-sun-was-formed-4-6-billion-years-ago-5399524%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20upcoming%20total%20solar%20eclipse%20is%20a%20special%20moment%20to%20reflect%20on%20our%20place%20in%20the%20universe%2C%20scientists%20have%20been%20studying%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20sun%20and%20the%20formation%20of%20our%20solar%20system%20for%20a%20long%20time.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-how-sun-was-formed-4-6-billion-years-ago-5399524%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-how-sun-was-formed-4-6-billion-years-ago-5399524%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-how-sun-was-formed-4-6-billion-years-ago-5399524%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Newly%20Declassified%20Documents%20Reveal%20What%20Nuclear%20War%20Would%20Look%20Like%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20increasingly%20uncertain%20world%2C%20the%20spectre%20of%20nuclear%20conflict%20remains%20a%20haunting%20possibility.%20The%20outbreak%20of%20such%20a%20war%20would%20unleash%20unimaginable%20chaos%20and%20devastation%20on%20a%20global%20scale.%20The%20global%20situation%20is%20arguably%20the%20most%20dangerous%20since%20the%20Cuban%20missile%20crisis%2C%20with%20the%20ongoing%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20conflicts%20brewing%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20Against%20this%20backdrop%2C%20Pulitzer%20Prize%20finalist%20Annie%20Jacobsen%20has%20frighteningly%20outlined%20in%20her%20book%20'%3Cem%3ENuclear%20War%3A%20A%20Scenario%3C%2Fem%3E'%20what%20will%20happen%20if%20a%20nuclear%20war%20breaks%20out%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20decades%2C%20people%20were%20under%20the%20assumption%20that%20the%20nuclear%20threat%20ended%20when%20the%20Berlin%20Wall%20went%20down.%20Nuclear%20weapons%20and%20the%20whole%20nomenclature%20around%20them%20have%20been%20so%20rarefied%20it's%20been%20reserved%20as%20a%20subject%20for%20those%20in%20the%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Jacobsen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbooks%2F2024%2Fmar%2F31%2Fannie-jacobsen-nuclear-war-scenario%5C%22%3Etold%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20book%20is%20based%20on%20interviews%20with%20presidential%20advisers%2C%20cabinet%20members%2C%20nuclear%20weapons%20engineers%20and%20countless%20experts%2C%20and%20newly%20declassified%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20presents%20a%20scenario%20for%20a%20nuclear%20war%2C%20set%20in%20the%20present%20day.%20It%20takes%20Robert%20Oppenheimer's%20famous%20quotation%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EBhagavad%20Gita%3C%2Fem%3E%20-%20%26quot%3BNow%20I%20am%20become%20Death%2C%20the%20destroyer%20of%20worlds%26quot%3B%20-%20to%20its%20logical%20conclusion%20by%20providing%20a%20second-by-second%2C%20minute-by-minute%20and%20hour-by-hour%20breakdown%20of%20the%20nuclear%20war%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nightmare%20scenario%20talks%20about%20North%20Korea%20launching%20a%20surprise%20missile%20attack%20against%20the%20US%2C%20leading%20Washington%20to%20respond%20with%20a%20salvo%20of%2050%20Minuteman%20III%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missiles%20(ICBMs)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fjoshweiss%2F2024%2F03%2F30%2Freview-annie-jacobsens-nuclear-war-a-scenario-will-make-you-start-worrying-and-hate-the-bomb%2F%3Fsh%3D7668a6337557%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20lead%20to%20chaos%2C%20mass%20deaths%20and%20hysteria%2C%20says%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20portrait%20of%20the%20Armageddon%20is%20made%20more%20impactful%20by%20depiction%20of%20people%20turning%20to%20ash%2C%20birds%20falling%20from%20the%20sky%20and%20survivors%20die%20in%20agony%20form%20acute%20radiation%20sickness.%20And%20those%20who%20manage%20to%20survive%20all%20of%20that%20receive%20the%20consolation%20prize%20that%20is%20the%20drastic%20climatological%20shift%20known%20as%20nuclear%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trigger%2C%20according%20to%20Ms%20Jacobsen's%20book%2C%20is%20a%20miscommunication%2C%20an%20unforeseen%20technological%20malfunction%2C%20as%20per%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E.%20She%20has%20not%20named%20any%20of%20the%20key%20players%20(presidents%2C%20dictators%2C%20spies%2C%20generals%20and%20radar%20technicians).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20jaw%20dropped%20at%20so%20much%20of%20what%20I%20learned%2C%20which%20was%20not%20classified%20but%20had%20just%20been%20removed%20or%20rather%20sanitised%20from%20the%20public%20discourse.%20I%20found%20myself%20constantly%20surprised%20by%20the%20insanity%20of%20what%20I%20learned%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20all%20there%20for%20the%20public%20to%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20author%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20outlet%20said%20the%20number%20of%20nuclear%20warheads%20have%20declined%20from%2070%2C000%20to%20just%20over%2012%2C000%2C%20but%20this%20number%20too%20is%20enough%20to%20reduce%20the%20Earth%20to%20a%20radioactive%20desert.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712577600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fmkkdkcl_nuclear-war-scenario_625x300_08_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fnewly-declassifi